Lab 4:

sudo adduser training

#It will prompt for password.. provide any passowrd

#Login to the user
su training

#try below activty
sudo apt-get update

#It will give an error

training is not in the sudoers file

--------------------

Lab 5:
    
sudo vi  /etc/sudoers 

#Press i <insert mode>

training  ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL

#You need to press esc+:+wq+! (escape colon wq !)

#Now test
su training
sudo apt-get update

